Neural Networks, Probabilistic Methods. 

Neural Networks: The paper discusses the use of multiversion neural-net systems to solve data-defined problems. It explains how these systems can be trained to learn from data and make predictions based on that learning. 

Probabilistic Methods: The paper also discusses the use of probabilistic methods in these neural-net systems, specifically Bayesian methods. It explains how these methods can be used to incorporate prior knowledge and uncertainty into the learning process.
